        <name>16.4.4 General power series radius of convergence</name>
        <questiontext>&lt;p class="HELM_exercise"&gt;Exercise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Determine the convergence of the general power series \[1-(x-1)+(x-1)^2-(x-1)^3+\cdots\]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;First find an expression for the general term:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; \(\displaystyle{\sum_{p=0}^\infty }\) [[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] so \(b_p=\) [[input:ans2]] [[validation:ans2]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[feedback:prt1]] [[feedback:prt2]]&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Now obtain the radius of convergence:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\(R=\) [[input:ans3]] [[validation:ans3]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;[[feedback:prt3]] &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Finally, decide on the convergence at \(|x - 1| = R\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When \(x - 1 = R\), the series is: [[input:ans4]] [[validation:ans4]] [[feedback:prt4]]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When \(x - 1 = -R\), the series is: [[input:ans5]] [[validation:ans5]] [[feedback:prt5]]&lt;/p&gt;</questiontext>
        <questiontextformat>1</questiontextformat>
        <generalfeedback>&lt;p&gt;First, we find an expresion for the general term:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;\[1-(x-{@a1@})+(x-{@a1@})^2-(x-{@a1@})^3+\dots = \sum_{p=0}^\infty {@ser@},\]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;so \( b_p={@b_p@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now we obtain the radius of convergence: \[ \lim_{p \to \infty} \left|\dfrac{b_p}{b_{p+1}}\right| = \lim_{p+1} \left|\dfrac{(-1)^p}{(-1)^{p+1}}\right| = 1\] Hence \(R={@R1@}\), so the series is absolutely convergent, and thus convergent, if \(|x-{@a1@}|&amp;lt;{@R1@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, we decide on the convergence of the series when \(|x - 1| = R = {@R1@}\).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the first case, we have \(x = 1 + R = {@R1+1@}\), and the series becomes&lt;/p&gt;
\[1 - 1 + 1 - 1 + \cdots,\]
&lt;p&gt;which is &lt;b&gt;divergent&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For the second case, we have \(x = 1 - R = {@1-R1@}\), and the series becomes&lt;/p&gt;
\[1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + \cdots,\]
&lt;p&gt;which is clearly &lt;b&gt;divergent&lt;/b&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</generalfeedback>
